Healthcare Specialist: Good morning! How can I help you today?
Patient: Hey doc, I been tryna eat better to help my heart. What kinda food should I be eatin'?
Healthcare Specialist: Well, it's important to focus on eating lots of fruits and vegetables. They can help keep your heart healthy. 
Patient: Oh, I see. What about fried food? Can I still have that sometimes?
Healthcare Specialist: It's best to limit fried food because it can be high in unhealthy fats. But you can have it in moderation.
Patient: Got it. What about salt? Should I be watchin' how much I eat?
Healthcare Specialist: Yes, it's important to watch your salt intake. Too much salt can make your heart work harder. Try to use herbs and spices instead of salt.
Patient: Okay, thanks for the tips, doc. What else should I be eatin'?
Healthcare Specialist: Whole grains like brown rice and whole wheat bread are good choices. They can help keep your heart healthy.
Patient: Sounds good. Any other foods I should be addin' to my diet?
Healthcare Specialist: Foods high in omega-3 fatty acids, like salmon and walnuts, are great for your heart. They can help reduce inflammation and improve heart health.
Patient: Alright, I'll make sure to add those to my grocery list. Thanks for all the info, doc.
Healthcare Specialist: You're welcome! Remember, eating a healthy diet is important for managing your heart failure. Let me know if you have any other questions.